rComments: worst thing about him is he doesn't record lectures OR post slides, so if you miss class ur screwed. he's pretty knowledgable tho and stresses the things you need to know for the exams. as an anglophone his french was pretty easy to understand. quizzes are also not too bad, fairly easy if u know the material but u often have barely enough time

He doesn't give the powerpoint and doesn't record his zoom calls, yet he records the oral presentations. He talks for 30 minutes+ of the same thing and goes in circles all the time, so it's easy to lose focus. Also, the midterm was ridiculously long for no reason, even if he hinted the question during class. Barely any feedback and hard to contact.

Beaucoup de personnes se plaignent du temps alloué pour les examens cependant, son cours est très clair et pas ennuyant, si vous prenez de bonnes notes et que vous étudiez bien, vous réussirez sans problème ! Les questions sont bien énoncées et les réponses sont courtes. La clé, cest vraiment de prendre des notes organisées. Très bon prof !

Took 1701 as an anglophone whose french is horrible and STILL understood everything; he's just that clear. People who say his evals are hard must not pay attention in class, because the structure of the lectures makes it very apparent what you need to know and what's just a tidbit of info. Engaging, clear, and considerate. Best prof i've had.

The class was interesting and i enjoyed listening to the lectures but even though i thought i had a very good understanding on the subject I never did so good on the test. You finish the test feeling confident and then you get your grade back confused on how you couldve gotten such a low grade.
He will get sidetracked a lot. You would think you did well on the exams but it's not as good as you thought it would be.

Good teacher. Teaches with passion and that can really get you engaged. Multiple choice exams, although you'd think you got a good grade when the exam is over, your grade isn't as good as you thought so still really need to study.

One of the greatest professors of all time. I am currently in his 1701 CRM (in french) class and he makes my day every time I listen to his lectures. He is the one teacher that explains clearly every thing and makes it fun to learn. So enthusiastic and caring! I definitely recommend Professor Dufresne!!!! THANK YOU!!

This is supposed to be a first year crim class but all of the questions on the exam are philosophical. Questions on exams are abstract and you arent allowed to ask questions. All concepts are abstract, the prof doesnt explain well and puts nothing on his slides. I have 90s in all my other classes and have never done so bad in a class.

Really good prof. His CRM1701 class is an Easy A if you show up to class and take notes. His powerpoints aren't filled in all that much but he repeats the important info over and over again so you really can't go wrong. No textbook which is nice. Go to his TA's study sessions, its a quick and easy review! I would definitely take his class again.

Si tu as besoin de prendre un cours a option qui est assez facile et intéressant, je suggère ce cours avec M. Dufresne. Il est très motivant pendant ses lectures et il répète clairement la matière importante qui va être dans les examens, donc il est important d'allé en classe. En plus, les lectures sont en ligne, donc tu sauve un peu d'argent.

Martin Dufresnes is the Bruce Willis of Criminology. He is really good at keeping the attention of his student and going to his TA's study sessions is a must! They make sure to give you all the information you need and answer all your questions.
Très bon professeur passionné par la discipline et qui transmet très bien son savoir. Disponible pour répondre aux questions et les attentes sont claire.
Super professeur! Très gentil, passionné et passionnant
AMAZING TEACHER! If you want to do good go to the discussion group it really helps, write your notes while he's since it can get very overwhelming because of how in dept he goes.

Fantastic prof. Really pleasant to listen to. He set's up study groups lead by his TA's before midterms and exams; if you don't go to those, you are literally throwing away your easy A. go to the review sessions!!!

Great class! Dufresne is a great prof. His lectures are interesting (funny too) and easy to follow. He is very clear on the big ideas, but you need to know some little details for MC. No textbook used for this class, all readings are accessible online. TA's are very helpful. Make sure to go to class.

Honestly a really great prof! His lectures are easy to follow and interesting, but you definitely have to go to class since he doesn't post much at all on Brightspace. He reiterates concepts so its a lot easier to remember too. If french isn't your first language, the multiple choice on midterms can be tricky. Overall, great prof!
C'est un vraiment bon Prof, il connait sa matière et garde l'intérêt des étudiants dans les cours. Si vous allez aux sessions de révision pour les mid-terms, les examens seront extrêmement faciles.

J'ai aimé le cours. Il garde l'attention du public, dans le bon sens du terme. Il est vraiment drôle! Il est important d'aller en classe, car ses power point sont légers. Le plus important est d'écouter en classe, prendre des notes et l'examen sera facile. Il prévient à l'avance des notions à étudier et revient souvent sur la matière.

Very good teacher, he obviously knows his things. Though his powerpoint are not on blackboard, he lets you know what's important. His midterms can be difficult and tricky though, you really need to understand the class. He won't answer questions during exams, so, be ready. Overall, l like this teacher.

Ce cours est très intéressant! Le projet de session est très intéressant, mais mettez-vous avec une personne de confiance, parce que vous allez passer la session avec! L'examen de mi-session est difficile, mais si t'étudies, t'es correct. Tout de même cours vraiment intéressant!

Justice pénale et technologie. Le cours est philosophique de A à Z.  Un examen de mi-session, une présentation orale et un examen de 50%  Si vous n'avez pas de facilité en philosophie : ce cours n'est pas pour vous.

Very clear and funny in his lectures. He conveys the subject matter well, and he always welcomes questions and discussions in class. Not being fluent in french, I had to ask him questions almost after every class. He was always very cordial and patient with me, even going out of his way to elaborate in English sometimes. Fav prof!

Good professor with very engaging and stimulating lectures, makes the students interested in learning. However didn't use powerpoint so may be difficult to narrow in on what you should know. Exams are quite difficult, you really have to prove you know the material inside out. Grading criteria wasn't discussed much.

The BEST prof!! 2 midterms and 1 final exam (all in the same format). The multiple choices are simple if you pay attention in class and the readings (short) are important for the short-answer questions. Prof is great, interesting and clear when it comes to explaining the material. He also always repeats himself and goes over what is important.
Un des meilleurs prof en CRM du programme francais. N'importe quel de ses cours est recommander.

Meilleur prof que j'ai eu dans mon premier semestre. Il y a certaine de mes autres classes que je manquais parce que je m'en foutais mais je n'ai jamais manqué un cours de CRIM 1701 la raison??.....MARTIN DUFRESNE :)
très bon professeur, très présent pour ses élèves, il organise même des groupes de discussion avant les examens avec ses assistantes pour récapituler la matière!!

Best Criminology Professor in the whole faculty. Very enthusiastic in his way of teaching, makes his lecture fun and refreshing. His slides are not meant to hold information, they're just reminders. YOU SHOULD BE IN CLASS taking down the notes, they are worth their weight in gold. Had him my freshman year in F:2009, going to have him again soon!:)

He's a good teacher. Generally keeps you interested. The thing is his slides are useful but not very detailed. And you feel like you understand the material and then he picks the RANDOMEST stuff for the midterms. Make sure you understand in your own words. I think that's the biggest thing with this guy. Could also be the way his T.A. correct dunno.

Excellent professeur... très naturel.  Ses diapos sont très clairs, tout comme son enseignement.  Les concepts sont très faciles à comprendre puisque ses explications sont simples.  Il est aussi très très drôle.

Le prof est vraiment excellent. C'est diapos sont pertinente lorsqu'on vient au cours et il est interessant. Le cours dur 3 heures et il reussi a tous nous garder eveiller. Les textes ne sont pas trop penible a lire et les examen sont totalement representatif de la matiere. Bravo.
Not condescending or cocky at all like the other student posted in fact he is quite the opposite.. if you go to class and listen you will do great in his class.
Very condescending in his teaching method; not understanding or sympathetic; too cocky for his own good. However, knows his craft very well. It's easy to get a good grade in his classes.
I could not have asked for a better prof than that.

Honestly, where are you going to find a Professor who truly treats you like a respectable human being and friend EVERY time she or he interacts with you? Look no further - Professor Dufresne is fantastic!!
Makes me laugh at every class!! Very interesting :)
No Comments
